<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="530" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">King of Italy</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Genovareggia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="center">Telegram.—Translation.</p>
                        <p>Delighted to have the visit of the beautiful vessel to which you have
                            been pleased to confide the mission of assisting at the fetes at Genoa.
                            I desire to thank you cordially for this friendly manifestation of good
                            will.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Victor Emanuel.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>